com.tomtom.speedtools.mongodb

Class MongoDBUpdate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tomtom.speedtools.mongodb.MongoDBUpdate

  • public class MongoDBUpdate
extends Object
    Utility to facilitate creating mongo update objects using mapper fields. Fields in nested objects can be addressed. Query values are type-safe. Example: 
     collection.update(
   new MongoDBQuery().
     eq(personMapper.lastName, "Henderson"),
   new MongoDBUpdate().
     set(personMapper.address.street, "Sunset blvd."));

      • pull

        @Nonnull
public <T> MongoDBUpdate pull(@Nonnull
                                       EntityMapper.Field<Collection<T>> f0,
                                       @Nonnull
                                       MongoDBQuery mongoDBQuery)
        Removes all occurrences of value from a field, if field is an array. If the field is present but is not an array, an error condition is raised. Mongo shell equivalent: 
         { $pull : { field : {field2: value} } }
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type.
        Parameters:
        f0 - The field that holds an array.
        mongoDBQuery - The query that matches an element in the array.
        Returns:
        This instance.
